<p><b>Finger binary</b> is a system for <a href="/wiki/Finger_counting" title="Finger counting">counting</a> and displaying <a href="/wiki/Binary_numeral_system" title="Binary numeral system">binary numbers</a> on the <a href="/wiki/Finger" title="Finger">fingers</a> and <a href="/wiki/Thumb" title="Thumb">thumbs</a> of one or more <a href="/wiki/Hand" title="Hand">hands</a>. It is possible to count from 0 to 31 (2<sup>5</sup>−1) using the fingers of a single hand, or from 0 through 1023 (2<sup>10</sup>−1) if both hands are used.</p>
